        -:  971://
        -:  972://    This checks the condition and if the condition is not satisfied
        -:  973://    it prints message about the condition violation, including the
        -:  974://    condition itself, plus additional message streamed into it, if any,
        -:  975://    and then it aborts the program. It aborts the program irrespective of
        -:  976://    whether it is built in the debug mode or not.
        -:  977:# define GTEST_CHECK_(condition) \
        -:  978:    GTEST_AMBIGUOUS_ELSE_BLOCKER_ \
        -:  979:    if (::testing::internal::IsTrue(condition)) \
        -:  980:      ; \
        -:  981:    else \
        -:  982:      GTEST_LOG_(FATAL) << "Condition " #condition " failed. "
