        -: 2071:// MSVC "deprecates" snprintf and issues warnings wherever it is used.  In
        -: 2072:// order to avoid these warnings, we need to use _snprintf or _snprintf_s on
        -: 2073:// MSVC-based platforms.  We map the GTEST_SNPRINTF_ macro to the appropriate
        -: 2074:// function in order to achieve that.  We use macro definition here because
        -: 2075:// snprintf is a variadic function.
        -: 2076:#if _MSC_VER && !GTEST_OS_WINDOWS_MOBILE
        -: 2077:// MSVC 2005 and above support variadic macros.
        -: 2078:# define GTEST_SNPRINTF_(buffer, size, format, ...) \
        -: 2079:     _snprintf_s(buffer, size, size, format, __VA_ARGS__)
        -: 2080:#elif defined(_MSC_VER)
        -: 2081:// Windows CE does not define _snprintf_s
        -: 2082:# define GTEST_SNPRINTF_ _snprintf
        -: 2083:#else
        -: 2084:# define GTEST_SNPRINTF_ snprintf
        -: 2085:#endif
